Wohyń [ˈvɔxɨɲ] is a village in Radzyń Podlaski County, Lublin Voivodeship, in eastern Poland. It is the seat of the gmina (administrative district) called Gmina Wohyń. It lies approximately 12 kilometres (7 mi) east of Radzyń Podlaski and 58 km (36 mi) north of the regional capital Lublin.The village has a population of 2,000.


